Currently there's no option to customize the page tree on a given space. This ability could increase the customization options for some teams, allowing a finer control over the space structure.

Some interesting cases would be : 
* Admin wants to hide a specific part of the page tree;
* Admin wants to display the current page only, on the page tree;
* Admin want to hide the pagetree altogether (instead of using the workaround suggested on [Move, copy, and hide pages|https://confluence.atlassian.com/confcloud/move-copy-and-hide-pages-724764858.html#Move,copy,andhidepages-Hidepages]

h3. Issue Summary
When any macro that accepts text input is placed under a Bold text, if you move the cursor to just before the macro (same line) and press backspace, it will break the macro.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Insert a Bold text and press <ENTER>;
# Insert any macro that accepts text input, such as the code block;
# Put the cursor just before the macro (at the same line)
# Press <BACKSPACE> (<DELETE> on Mac);

h3. Expected Results
It should delete the line break before the macro.

h3. Actual Results
It breaks/ split the macro element.
 !code_block_break.gif|width=700px! 

h3. Notes
Some of the affected macros:
* page properties;
* info;
* code block;
* section;
* basically any macro that accepts text inputs.

h3. Workaround
Use Ctrl+Z or Command+Z to undo the action and restore the macro.
